WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.394
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12.882 --> 00:15.885
-♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

00:17.017 --> 00:20.890
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

00:21.021 --> 00:24.589
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HAVE SOMEBODY ♪

00:24.720 --> 00:27.984
♪ WHEN THE EDGE OF
SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT ♪

00:28.115 --> 00:30.726
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY

00:30.856 --> 00:34.034
♪ IT'S GONNA BE ALRIGHT

00:36.949 --> 00:38.821
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

00:38.951 --> 00:42.303
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

00:45.393 --> 00:49.353
♪ I'LL BE READY,
I'LL BE READY ♪

00:49.484 --> 00:53.357
♪ WHENEVER YOU FEAR,
OH, DON'T YOU FEAR ♪

00:53.488 --> 00:56.012
♪ I'LL BE READY

00:56.621 --> 00:59.711
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS ♪

00:59.842 --> 01:02.888
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

01:20.645 --> 01:22.604
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

01:22.734 --> 01:26.086
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

01:29.480 --> 01:33.310
♪ I'LL BE READY,
I'LL BE READY ♪

01:33.441 --> 01:37.488
♪ WHENEVER YOU FEAR,
OH, DON'T YOU FEAR ♪

01:37.619 --> 01:40.100
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:41.101 --> 01:43.799
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:43.929 --> 01:46.454
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

01:46.584 --> 01:50.893
[THEME MUSIC]

02:01.947 --> 02:04.298
[GENTLE MUSIC]

02:08.039 --> 02:11.522
[LAUGHTER]

02:24.056 --> 02:25.232
-I COULDN'T WAIT TO GET HERE.

02:25.362 --> 02:26.450
HI, HOW ARE YA?

02:26.581 --> 02:27.582
-GOOD MORNING.

02:35.372 --> 02:36.547
-THERE.
-I'M GOING DOWN.

02:36.678 --> 02:38.245
-BE CAREFUL.

02:42.118 --> 02:43.511
-WATCH OUT, BILLY!

02:51.171 --> 02:56.393
[ROARING ENGINES]

03:13.889 --> 03:15.195
-CAROLINE: ARE THOSE
THE SAME TWO GUYS

03:15.325 --> 03:16.587
YOU READ THE RIOT ACT
TO YESTERDAY?

03:16.718 --> 03:19.590
-YUP, AND SOMEBODY'S
GONNA GET HURT.

03:19.721 --> 03:20.722
LET'S GO.

03:26.031 --> 03:27.642
-LET'S GET OUT OF HERE!
-GO!

03:32.124 --> 03:33.517
-ALL RIGHT, WE CAN RADIO
THE BAYWATCH SCARAB,

03:33.648 --> 03:35.345
SEE IF THEY CAN
CATCH UP TO THEM.

03:35.476 --> 03:37.652
-YEAH, AND THEN THEY'LL DO
EXACTLY WHAT THEY DID YESTERDAY

03:37.782 --> 03:40.002
AFTER I CITED THEM FOR NOT
HAVING REGISTRATION NUMBERS

03:40.132 --> 03:43.223
ON THEIR WAVE RUNNERS--
PICK ANOTHER BEACH.

03:46.313 --> 03:49.751
[GRUNTING]

03:49.881 --> 03:54.930
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

03:55.496 --> 03:56.627
-HELP!

03:56.758 --> 04:01.502
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

04:14.166 --> 04:15.429
-LOU?

04:30.618 --> 04:34.622
[BREATHING HARD]

04:57.906 --> 05:00.822
[SIRENS]

05:22.539 --> 05:24.889
-HE WENT DOWN RIGHT
HERE, I'VE GOT A CRAMP.

05:25.020 --> 05:28.284
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

05:52.482 --> 05:53.875
-MITCH: HEY, YOU ALRIGHT?

06:10.500 --> 06:12.154
-LOU!
-[SIRENS]

06:12.937 --> 06:14.112
ARE YOU ALRIGHT?

06:14.243 --> 06:15.375
-MITCH: HE'S ALL RIGHT,
HE'S OKAY.

06:15.505 --> 06:17.202
[SIRENS]

06:17.333 --> 06:18.378
-I'VE GOT A CRAMP.

06:18.508 --> 06:20.858
-OH HONEY.
OH HONEY.

06:20.989 --> 06:22.251
-THANKS.
-IT'S ALRIGHT.

06:22.382 --> 06:24.209
-DID HE TAKE IN
MUCH SALT WATER?

06:24.340 --> 06:25.994
-NO, NOT TOO MUCH.
YOU CAN TAKE HIM BACK
TO HEADQUARTERS

06:26.124 --> 06:27.604
AND CHECK HIM OUT
BEFORE WE RELEASE HIM.

06:27.735 --> 06:29.389
-OKAY, YOU GOT IT.
-CAN I GO WITH YOU, PLEASE?

06:29.519 --> 06:31.434
-THAT'D BE FINE MA'AM.
-OH THANK YOU, THANK YOU.

06:36.396 --> 06:38.485
-WELL THAT MAKES TWO OF
YOU WITH A CRAMP TODAY.

06:41.836 --> 06:43.228
-ARE YOU OKAY?

06:43.359 --> 06:45.274
-ACTUALLY, I'M NOT
FEELING MYSELF TODAY.

06:45.405 --> 06:46.449
LOOK, I'M SORRY.

06:46.580 --> 06:48.016
-THERE'S NOTHING
TO BE SORRY FOR.

06:48.146 --> 06:49.539
-ANY ONE OF USE COULD
HAVE GOTTEN A CRAMP.

06:51.498 --> 06:52.629
-YOU WATCH HER WATER, HUH?

06:52.760 --> 06:54.370
-OKAY.
-LOOK

06:54.501 --> 06:55.763
WHY DON'T YOU GO HOME AND GET SOME REST?

06:55.893 --> 06:57.286
-NO, NO, NO, I'M FINE.
-NO, NO, NO

06:57.417 --> 06:59.767
I WANT YOU TO
GO HOME AND GET SOME REST.

07:00.376 --> 07:02.944
LIFEGUARD'S ORDERS, HUH?
COME ON.

07:12.954 --> 07:14.434
HELLO?

07:14.564 --> 07:15.478
-I'M SORRY, I GOT HERE
AS FAST AS I COULD.

07:15.609 --> 07:17.262
-IT'S ALL RIGHT, YOU GOT IT?

07:17.393 --> 07:18.742
-GOT WHAT?

07:18.873 --> 07:21.005
-AH, COME ON, I'M
NERVOUS ENOUGH ALREADY.

07:21.136 --> 07:22.877
-OF COURSE I HAVE IT, HERE.

07:29.971 --> 07:31.059
-WOW.

07:31.712 --> 07:32.974
IS THAT BEAUTIFUL OR WHAT?

07:33.583 --> 07:34.671
-STEPHANIE: IT IS BEAUTIFUL.

07:36.804 --> 07:38.501
-WHAT IF TRACY SAYS NO? I MEAN,

07:40.024 --> 07:41.852
GAIL SAID NO WHEN I
ASKED HER TO MARRY ME.

07:41.983 --> 07:44.202
-I KNOW HOW BADLY
YOU WERE HURT BY GAIL,

07:44.768 --> 07:46.466
BUT YOU AND GAIL
WEREN'T MEANT TO BE,

07:47.815 --> 07:49.164
AND TRACY AND YOU ARE.

07:49.294 --> 07:50.557
YOU'RE LIKE,

07:52.341 --> 07:55.213
LIKE TWO HALVES OF A SOUL
THAT HAVE FOUND ONE ANOTHER.

07:55.866 --> 07:57.825
TRACY IS COMPLETELY
IN LOVE WITH YOU.

08:00.175 --> 08:01.829
-YOU KNOW I LOVE HER
MORE THAN ANYTHING.

08:06.355 --> 08:07.399
THANKS.

08:13.797 --> 08:14.842
TO US.

08:21.936 --> 08:23.546
REMEMBER THE FIRST
TIME WE CAME HERE?

08:25.940 --> 08:27.376
-OUR FIRST KISS.

08:29.247 --> 08:31.511
AND I REMEMBER THE
SECOND TIME WE CAME HERE.

08:33.643 --> 08:37.385
-NOW THAT IS A DAY
I'LL NEVER FORGET.

08:54.490 --> 08:55.578
-OH, MITCH.

08:58.625 --> 08:59.713
-WILL YOU MARRY ME?

09:02.890 --> 09:04.544
-I LIED TO YOU TODAY, MITCH.

09:07.111 --> 09:08.635
I DIDN'T GET A CRAMP.

09:11.420 --> 09:13.422
I COULDN'T MAKE IT
TO THE VICTIM BECAUSE

09:13.553 --> 09:15.380
I DIDN'T HAVE THE STAMINA.

09:16.512 --> 09:19.428
-HEY, HEY, WE
ALL HAVE OFF DAYS.

09:21.386 --> 09:23.084
THIS IS WHY YOU'RE
UPSET I'M THRILLED.

09:23.214 --> 09:26.653
I MEAN, I THOUGHT MAYBE YOU
DIDN'T WANT TO MARRY ME.

09:28.524 --> 09:30.570
-THIS ISN'T ABOUT
WHAT I WANT, MITCH.

09:32.746 --> 09:34.574
I CAN'T BE A
LIFEGUARD ANY LONGER.

09:37.620 --> 09:40.928
THERE'S NOTHING THAT I'D LIKE
MORE THAN TO BE YOUR WIFE...

09:43.234 --> 09:44.279
-WHAT?

09:47.978 --> 09:49.023
DO YOU LOVE ME?

09:51.547 --> 09:54.289
-OH, MITCH, I LOVE YOU LIKE
I'VE NEVER LOVED ANYONE,

09:55.595 --> 09:57.858
IN A WAY I NEVER KNEW POSSIBLE,

09:58.859 --> 10:00.208
BUT I CAN'T MARRY YOU.

10:01.557 --> 10:06.780
[SOMBER MUSIC]

10:22.186 --> 10:23.361
-WHY?

10:27.714 --> 10:29.106
-I'M DYING.

10:32.632 --> 10:34.329
I'VE GOT CANCER, MITCH.

10:36.810 --> 10:39.421
THE DOCTORS TOLD ME I'VE
GOT TWO MONTHS LEFT...

10:39.551 --> 10:43.468
TWO MONTHS AGO. I'M
ALREADY ON BORROWED TIME.

10:51.172 --> 10:52.869
-WELL, THERE MUST BE
SOMETHING THE DOCTORS CAN DO.

10:53.000 --> 10:56.525
-IT'S TOO LATE, SO I
WENT OFF CHEMOTHERAPY.

10:56.656 --> 10:58.222
I JUST, I COULDN'T
TAKE IT ANY LONGER.

11:04.228 --> 11:05.099
-ARE YOU IN PAIN?

11:07.101 --> 11:08.798
-NOT NEARLY AS PAINFUL AS THIS.

11:10.365 --> 11:12.019
-THIS IS A MISTAKE, RIGHT?

11:14.761 --> 11:16.501
HOW COULD I NOT KNOW?

11:17.154 --> 11:18.939
-BECAUSE I HID IT FROM YOU.

11:19.983 --> 11:21.419
THE ONLY MISTAKE WAS MINE...

11:22.420 --> 11:24.509
IN ALLOWING YOU TO
FALL IN LOVE WITH ME.

11:24.640 --> 11:26.294
-NO, NO, NO.

11:27.208 --> 11:28.513
THAT WASN'T A MISTAKE.

11:35.042 --> 11:37.305
I'LL TAKE WHATEVER TIME
WE HAVE LEFT TOGETHER.

11:45.139 --> 11:46.706
I LOVE YOU, TRACY.

11:48.446 --> 11:49.883
-I LOVE YOU TOO.

12:11.861 --> 12:13.689
-HOBIE: HEY, DAD.
-PAL.

12:13.820 --> 12:15.125
-HOW COME YOU'RE NOT AT WORK?

12:16.431 --> 12:17.867
-I'M NOT GOING IN TODAY.

12:19.564 --> 12:21.436
AS A MATTER OF FACT I'M
TAKING A LITTLE TIME OFF,

12:21.566 --> 12:22.959
I WON'T BE GOING IN FOR A WHILE.

12:23.090 --> 12:24.091
-WHY NOT?

12:24.221 --> 12:25.135
SOMETHING THE MATTER?

12:25.266 --> 12:26.746
-TRACY, SHE'S UH...

12:28.530 --> 12:30.401
SHE'S SICK AND SHE NEEDS ME.

12:33.143 --> 12:34.275
-WHAT'S ALL THIS STUFF?

12:34.884 --> 12:36.277
YOU GOING ON A TRIP?

12:36.407 --> 12:38.496
-YEAH, I WAS THINKING OF
SURPRISING HER YOU KNOW,

12:38.627 --> 12:40.237
AND TAKING HER SOMEWHERE.

12:40.847 --> 12:42.065
WHY DON'T YOU HELP
ME PICK OUT A PLACE?

12:42.196 --> 12:43.806
THERE'S SOME
AWESOME PLACES HERE.

12:43.937 --> 12:46.156
-SURE, BUT IF SHE'S SICK,

12:46.287 --> 12:47.636
WHY DON'T YOU WAIT
TIL SHE'S BETTER?

12:50.639 --> 12:52.075
-TRACY'S NOT GONNA GET BETTER.

12:52.206 --> 12:57.167
[SOMBER MUSIC]

13:15.185 --> 13:16.578
-GRANDMA WANTED TO TAKE GRANDPA

13:16.708 --> 13:18.188
ON A TRIP BEFORE
HE WAS GONNA DIE.

13:19.711 --> 13:21.235
TRACY'S NOT GONNA DIE IS SHE?

13:24.455 --> 13:25.892
-SHE'S REAL SICK.

13:26.022 --> 13:28.459
-DAD, I CAN HANDLE THE TRUTH.

13:28.590 --> 13:30.244
I'M NOT A LITTLE KID ANYMORE.

13:33.247 --> 13:35.118
-NO, NO, YOU'RE NOT, ARE YOU?

13:36.206 --> 13:39.253
-JUST TELL ME, IS TRACY DYING?

13:46.390 --> 13:47.435
-YEAH.

13:49.741 --> 13:51.395
YEAH, TRACY'S DYING.

14:13.504 --> 14:17.334
[ENGINES ROARING]

14:17.465 --> 14:22.557
[SHOUTING]

14:32.872 --> 14:37.093
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

15:05.730 --> 15:06.949
-LADY: STOP IT!

15:07.080 --> 15:11.867
[SHOUTING]
[ROARING ENGINES]

15:37.980 --> 15:40.635
-YEAH! GOOD ONE!
LET'S GO!

15:40.765 --> 15:45.553
[GASPING]

15:48.338 --> 15:50.340
-HERE YOU GO, EVERYTHING'S
GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

15:50.993 --> 15:51.951
COME ON.

15:54.388 --> 15:55.955
-COME ON, GET OUT OF HERE!

15:59.349 --> 16:01.003
[SHOUTING]
THAT'S FUN!

16:01.134 --> 16:03.440
WE GAVE YOU SOMETHING TO DO!

16:08.750 --> 16:10.056
-LISTEN, ARE YOU SURE THOSE ARE

16:10.186 --> 16:11.579
THE SAME TWO GUYS
ON THE WAVE RUNNER?

16:11.709 --> 16:13.146
-I'D KNOW THEM IN A
SEA OF WAVE RUNNERS.

16:13.276 --> 16:14.799
THEIR STYLE IS UNMISTAKABLE.

16:14.930 --> 16:16.627
THEY STILL DON'T HAVE
REGISTRATION NUMBERS

16:16.758 --> 16:17.846
AND THEY'RE GONNA KILL SOMEONE.

16:17.977 --> 16:19.282
I'M GONNA SEE MITCH.

16:24.679 --> 16:26.115
[KNOCKING]

16:27.421 --> 16:28.422
-HEY.

16:28.552 --> 16:29.510
-STEPHANIE: HI.

16:29.640 --> 16:31.686
-MITCH AROUND?
-UH NO.

16:32.469 --> 16:36.038
ACTUALLY, YOU TWO ARE JUST THE
PEOPLE I WANTED TO SPEAK WITH.

16:38.040 --> 16:39.999
THERE'S NO EASY WAY TO SAY THIS.

16:42.479 --> 16:44.873
TRACY'S DYING, SHE'S GOT CANCER.

16:45.874 --> 16:46.744
-TRACY...

16:53.577 --> 16:54.883
IS THERE ANYTHING WE CAN DO?

16:55.014 --> 16:56.841
-YES, AS A MATTER
OF FACT THERE IS.

16:56.972 --> 16:59.105
MATT AND CJ WON'T BE
BACK TIL NEXT WEEK,

16:59.235 --> 17:01.846
SO WE'RE SHORTHANDED AS IT
IS, AND NOW MITCH IS TAKING

17:01.977 --> 17:03.196
A LEAVE OF ABSENCE
TO BE WITH TRACY

17:03.326 --> 17:05.328
BECAUSE SHE DOESN'T
HAVE MUCH TIME.

17:05.936 --> 17:08.810
SO, I REALLY NEED YOU GUYS
TO HANDLE THINGS AROUND HERE.

17:08.940 --> 17:11.160
I'M JUST SWAMPED WITH
PAPERWORK AND TOWER ASSIGNMENTS

17:11.290 --> 17:14.381
AND I PROMISED MITCH THAT I'D
HELP HIM WITH HOBIE, SO...

17:14.511 --> 17:17.906
-HEY, DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT,
WE'LL TAKE CARE OF EVERYTHING.

17:18.559 --> 17:19.820
-THANK YOU.

17:19.951 --> 17:21.474
-NO PROBLEM, RIGHT, CAROLINE?

17:23.564 --> 17:25.695
-RIGHT. OF COURSE NOT.

17:29.048 --> 17:30.310
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

17:31.267 --> 17:33.269
-GIVE HER MY LOVE?
-YEAH.

17:34.227 --> 17:37.317
OH, I GOTTA RUN, I'M
PICKING UP HOBIE AT SCHOOL.

17:38.057 --> 17:39.623
OH, EXCUSE ME.

17:39.754 --> 17:42.061
LOGAN, WHEN YOU CAME IN
YOU WERE LOOKING FOR MITCH.

17:42.191 --> 17:43.497
-OH, IT'S NOTHING REALLY.

17:43.627 --> 17:45.977
I'LL TAKE CARE OF
IT, NO WORRIES.

17:46.108 --> 17:47.022
-OKAY.

17:57.859 --> 17:59.426
-TRACY: IT'S SO PEACEFUL HERE.

18:00.514 --> 18:02.429
I FEEL SAFE AND PROTECTED.

18:03.734 --> 18:06.041
LIKE TOMORROW CAN'T FIND US.

18:09.740 --> 18:11.264
-OH, I ALMOST FORGOT.

18:12.787 --> 18:15.964
THE TRAVEL BROCHURES, I MEAN
THERE ARE SO MANY PLACES TO GO

18:16.095 --> 18:18.314
I THINK THAT WE SHOULD
JUST GO EVERYWHERE.

18:19.446 --> 18:22.579
-LIKE TRYING TO CRAM A
LIFETIME OF LIVING INTO,

18:23.102 --> 18:24.973
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
HOW LONG I'VE GOT.

18:25.713 --> 18:28.368
ACCORDING TO THE DOCTORS, I
SHOULDN'T EVEN BE HERE TODAY.

18:28.498 --> 18:30.021
-DOCTORS CAN BE WRONG.

18:30.152 --> 18:32.720
LOOK, YOU'RE ALIVE TODAY,
THAT'S WHAT MATTERS.

18:34.330 --> 18:35.897
NOW COME ON, ANYWHERE
IN THE WORLD.

18:36.027 --> 18:38.204
YOUR WISH IS MY COMMAND.

18:38.334 --> 18:40.554
-OH, I DON'T WANT A TRIP.

18:42.208 --> 18:45.211
DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND?
WHAT I WANT IS TIME

18:45.341 --> 18:46.995
AND YOU CAN'T GIVE THAT TO ME.

18:47.648 --> 18:49.171
NO ONE CAN.

18:52.000 --> 18:54.785
I JUST WANT TO BE WITH YOU
MITCH, I DON'T CARE WHAT WE DO,

18:54.916 --> 18:58.702
I DON'T CARE WHERE WE GO,
I JUST WANT TO BE WITH YOU.

19:00.443 --> 19:01.705
FOR AS LONG AS WE'VE GOT.

19:30.343 --> 19:35.435
[SHOUTING]
[ROARING ENGINES]

19:48.274 --> 19:49.405
-HEY, MAN!

19:56.630 --> 19:58.675
ALL RIGHT!
-WOW. THAT WAS WILD.

19:58.806 --> 20:00.895
-WHOO! WHAT A DAY!

20:05.900 --> 20:07.423
-I'M IMPOUNDING
YOUR WAVE RUNNERS.

20:07.554 --> 20:09.338
-WHAT FOR?

20:09.469 --> 20:10.818
-RECKLESS DRIVING, YOU ALMOST
HIT A GIRL ON A WIND SURFER.

20:10.948 --> 20:12.646
-YOU CAN'T PROVE THAT.

20:12.776 --> 20:14.343
-WELL, I CAN PROVE YOU DON'T
HAVE REGISTRATION NUMBERS.

20:14.474 --> 20:16.476
I CITED YOU FOR THAT YESTERDAY.

20:17.259 --> 20:19.130
SO TODAY, MY FRIENDS,
I'M IMPOUNDING THEM.

20:19.261 --> 20:20.784
HAND OVER YOUR KEYS.

20:20.915 --> 20:22.090
-NO WAY, MAN.

20:22.221 --> 20:23.613
-FINE, HAVE IT YOUR WAY.

20:26.225 --> 20:28.139
-MY DAD'LL JUST GO
BUY ME ANOTHER ONE.

20:28.270 --> 20:30.577
-OH YEAH, AND WHAT WILL
YOUR DADDY DO FOR YOU

20:30.707 --> 20:32.100
WHEN YOU KILL AN
INNOCENT PERSON?

20:50.640 --> 20:52.120
-HI. WHAT'S GOING ON?

20:53.426 --> 20:56.472
-WELL, I WAS JUST
DOING SOME WRITING.

20:56.603 --> 20:59.693
I WAS GONNA TAKE THESE
CARDS OVER TO TRACY'S PLACE

20:59.823 --> 21:01.912
YOU KNOW, AND PUT THEM
ALL OVER THE ROOM.

21:02.826 --> 21:03.958
-SHE'LL LOVE THAT.

21:05.916 --> 21:08.005
HOW'S SHE DOING, MITCH?

21:08.136 --> 21:10.181
-WELL, SHE'S DOING A HELL
OF A LOT BETTER THAN I AM,
THAT'S FOR SURE.

21:11.226 --> 21:13.228
-YOU'RE STILL REELING
FROM THE SHOCK, YOU KNOW.

21:17.537 --> 21:18.625
WE ALL ARE.

21:20.279 --> 21:21.715
I THINK TRACY'S FARTHER ALONG

21:21.845 --> 21:23.630
IN THE ACCEPTANCE
PROCESS THAN ANY OF US.

21:25.936 --> 21:27.286
ESPECIALLY YOU.

21:28.635 --> 21:30.941
-YOU KNOW, STEPH, THIS WHOLE
THING IS LIKE A NIGHTMARE.

21:32.639 --> 21:35.729
IT'S LIKE I KEEP TELLING
MYSELF TO RELAX, YOU KNOW,

21:35.859 --> 21:37.208
IT'S ONLY A BAD DREAM.

21:39.602 --> 21:40.647
BUT I DON'T WAKE UP.

21:42.823 --> 21:44.172
I'M TRYING TO ACT NORMAL,

21:44.303 --> 21:46.305
WELL, I DON'T KNOW WHAT
NORMAL IS ANYMORE!

21:48.481 --> 21:50.134
IT'S UNBELIEVABLE.

21:50.265 --> 21:53.181
HOW COULD SOMEBODY SO
BEAUTIFUL AND VITAL BE DYING?

21:57.316 --> 22:01.189
YOU KNOW, MY DAD DIED
AND MY MOM MISSES HIM,

22:01.320 --> 22:03.191
BUT SHE'S GOT A
LIFETIME OF MEMORIES.

22:03.322 --> 22:04.932
-AND YOU FEEL CHEATED.
-YES!

22:05.062 --> 22:06.455
YES!

22:07.195 --> 22:09.240
-THEN DON'T LET
ANYONE OR ANYTHING

22:09.371 --> 22:11.242
CHEAT YOU OUT OF THE TIME
YOU HAVE LEFT WITH TRACY.

22:12.940 --> 22:15.072
AND DON'T USE UP YOUR
ENERGY BEING ANGRY.

22:21.035 --> 22:23.124
-I JUST DON'T KNOW HOW
TO TURN THE ANGER OFF.

22:23.951 --> 22:25.300
I DON'T KNOW.

22:25.431 --> 22:27.302
-WELL, THEN YOU'RE
DYING TOO, MITCH,

22:27.433 --> 22:29.783
BECAUSE ANGER
TAKES NO PRISONERS.

22:29.913 --> 22:31.959
IT WILL EAT YOU UP
FROM THE INSIDE OUT

22:32.089 --> 22:33.177
AND LEAVE YOU WITH NOTHING.

22:37.268 --> 22:38.661
WHEN SOMETHING LIKE THIS HAPPENS

22:38.792 --> 22:41.447
IT'S DIFFICULT TO
MAKE SENSE OF IT ALL,

22:42.404 --> 22:46.147
TO FIND ANY SILVER
LINING, BUT WE ALL KNOW

22:46.277 --> 22:49.324
WE'RE GONNA DIE EVENTUALLY,
MOST OF US JUST DON'T KNOW WHEN,

22:49.455 --> 22:51.544
OR WHEN OUR LOVED
ONES ARE GONNA DIE,

22:52.196 --> 22:55.286
BUT WHEN WE DO.
